  05 Nov 2005; Mark Loeser <halcy0n@gentoo.org> libdvdread-0.9.4-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on x86; bug #111134

  04 Nov 2005; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org>
  libdvdread-0.9.4-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc wrt #111134

  01 Nov 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  -libdvdread-0.9.3.ebuild:
  Remove old ebuilds.

  03 Sep 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libdvdread-0.9.3.ebuild, libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild,
  libdvdread-0.9.4-r1.ebuild:
  Don't install COPYING and INSTALL files.

  28 Feb 2005; Kito <kito@gentoo.org> libdvdread-0.9.4-r1.ebuild,
  libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild:
  0.9.4 stable on ppc-macos. 0.9.4-r1 add --with-libdvdcss=/usr to fix linking
  on darwin

  07 Feb 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org>
  libdvdread-0.9.4-r1.ebuild:
  now the dodoc call works again. fixes #81150

  05 Feb 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org>
  libdvdread-0.9.4-r1.ebuild:
  renamed ifo_dump binary to ifo_dump_dvdread to avoid collision with the ogle
  one. see #80837

*libdvdread-0.9.4-r1 (28 Jan 2005)

  28 Jan 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org>
  +libdvdread-0.9.4-r1.ebuild:
  made changes which were suggested by Stefan Briesenick <sbriesen@gmx.de>.
  fixes bug #52498. applied a patch, therefor going back to ~arch and revision
  bump.

  17 Dec 2004; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64

  24 Sep 2004; kito@gentoo.org libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild:
  added ~ppc-macos keyword. closes bug 59636

  29 Aug 2004; Tom Gall <tgall@gentoo.org> libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild:
  added ~ppc64, bug #60786

  23 Aug 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org>
  libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild:
  gnuconfig_update in src_unpack; use emake; tidy

  21 Aug 2004; Hardave Riar <hardave@gentoo.org> libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild:
  Added ~mips keyword and gnuconfig_update fix

  14 Apr 2004; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> libdvdread-0.9.4.ebuild:
